The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Adhunik Metaliks Ltd has registered a 74 per cent growth in net sales at Rs 735.75 crore for the year ended March 31 against Rs 423.78 crore in 2005-06. Profit before tax increased 56 per cent to Rs 85.77 crore from Rs 55.10 crore a year ago. Profit after tax rose 130 per cent to Rs 77.47 crore from Rs 33.71 crore. The board has recommended a dividend of 10 per cent for 2006-07 against 5 per cent paid in the previous year.

 Gemini Communication Ltd has posted a 54 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 18.08 crore for the year ended March 31 compared with Rs 11.74 crore a year ago. Total income grew 28 per cent to 162.14 crore from 126.51 crore in the previous year. The board has recommended a dividend of 20 per cent on the paid-up equity shares of the company. 

 HOV Services has posted a 73.7 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 6.7 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31 against Rs 3.9 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. Total income for the quarter rose to Rs 111.3 crore from Rs 45.1 crore. 

 Tata group company Nelito has recorded a 35 per cent growth in turnover at Rs 46 crore for 2006-07. Profit before tax jumped to Rs 9.36 crore from Rs 1.86 crore a year ago. Profit after tax rose to Rs 5.78 crore from Rs 0.61 crore in the previous year. Nelito has declared a dividend of 20 per cent. 

 Tata Consultancy Services has received the first annual Distinguished Corporate Partner award from the Bourns College of Engineering, University of California. The award recognises TCSs support to advance superior technology, research and service to the university and local community.

 Diana Tea Company Ltd plans to use a portion of its 200 hectares of unutilised land for alternate crop cultivation. The company produces about 5 million kg of black tea per year.

 Shree Rajasthan Syntex Ltd has registered a net profit of Rs 4.77 crore in the year ended March 31 compared with Rs 2.63 crore a year ago. Gross profit was Rs 17.56 crore in the year. Its turnover was Rs 298.6 crore against Rs 163.1 crore in the previous fiscal.

 Strides Arcolab Ltd will acquire the fermentation assets of Italy-based Disapa. The acquisition will be carried out through an SPV incorporated in Italy, which will be owned by Strides Arcolab International Ltd. 

 Head amp; Shoulders has launched anti-dandruff shampoo H amp;S Intensive Solutions. The product is priced at Rs 159 for 220 ml, Rs 59 for 70 ml and Rs 4 for a 7.5 ml sachet.

